    <body>
      <entry xml:id="entry_særæppæloj" xml:lang="os-x-digor" abv:completeness="incomplete">
        <form xml:id="form_d3999e66" type="lemma"><orth>særæppæloj</orth></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense xml:id="sense_d3999e69">
          <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>хвастун</q>
          </abv:tr>
          <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>bouncer</q>
          </abv:tr>
        </sense>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Сложение из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/>
          <gloss><q>голова</q></gloss> и <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>æppæloj</w></mentioned> от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æppælyn"/>
          <gloss><q>хвалить</q></gloss>. Синонимичное <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>xī-ppæloj</w></mentioned>
          <gloss><q rendition="#rend_doublequotes">хвалящий себя (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_xī"/>)</q></gloss> показывает, что <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/> заменяет здесь
          возвратное местоимение.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">It is a compounding of <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/>
          <gloss><q>head</q></gloss> and <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>æppæloj</w></mentioned> from
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æppælyn"/>
          <gloss><q>to compliment</q></gloss>. The synonymous expression <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w>xī-ppæloj</w></mentioned>
          <gloss><q rendition="#rend_doublequotes">one who compliments oneself (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_xī"/>)</q></gloss> shows that <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/>
          replaces the reflexive pronoun here.</etym>
      </entry>
